]}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 28, the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Texas ruled that the lawsuit can proceed, and that there is evidence the Biden administration continued awarding taxpayer cash to UNRWA even after Congress blocked funding to that group due to its support for Hamas's military infrastructure.\", \"from\": 31074, \"to\": 31380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31139, \"end\": 31144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"score\": 0.9999992708814418, \"rank\": 6.943366025347666e-07, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas\"}, {\"begin\": 31212, \"end\": 31232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 0.688817904721823, \"rank\": 0.4517449879512682, \"text\": \"Biden administration\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidency_of_Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 31269, \"end\": 31274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UNRWA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNRWA\"}, {\"begin\": 31286, \"end\": 31294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 0.9999980914531102, \"rank\": 1.251197073493647e-06, \"text\": \"Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}, {\"begin\": 31348, \"end\": 31353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"score\": 0.9999999725238243, \"rank\": 2.7476149860104087e-08, \"text\": \"Hamas\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 31077, \"to\": 31081}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. District Court\", \"from\": 31086, \"to\": 31109}, {\"ngram\": \"the Northern District\", \"from\": 31114, \"to\": 31135}, {\"ngram\": \"the lawsuit\", \"from\": 31156, \"to\": 31167}, {\"ngram\": \"evidence\", \"from\": 31199, \"to\": 31207}, {\"ngram\": \"awarding taxpayer cash\", \"from\": 31243, \"to\": 31265}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 31303, \"to\": 31310}, {\"ngram\": \"that group\", \"from\": 31314, \"to\": 31324}, {\"ngram\": \"its support\", \"from\": 31332, \"to\": 31343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"https://www.gatestoneinstitute.org/20811/biden-administration-donates-to-hamas If, under French law, it constitutes criminal \\\"hate speech\\\" to complain about what's perceived as an insult to one's religion, would not it also be criminal \\\"hate speech\\\" to ridicule one's religion, as the \\\"Dionysus Last Supper\\\" appeared to do?\", \"from\": 31382, \"to\": 31706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 31472, \"end\": 31482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9999491566543994, \"rank\": 5.0664144794222546e-05, \"text\": \"French law\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"https://www.gatestoneinstitute.org/20811/biden-administration-donates-to-hamas\", \"from\": 31382, \"to\": 31460}, {\"ngram\": \"criminal \\\"hate speech\", \"from\": 31498, \"to\": 31519}, {\"ngram\": \"an insult\", \"from\": 31559, \"to\": 31568}, {\"ngram\": \"one's religion\", \"from\": 31572, \"to\": 31586}, {\"ngram\": \"criminal \\\"hate speech\", \"from\": 31609, \"to\": 31630}, {\"ngram\": \"one's religion\", \"from\": 31644, \"to\": 31658}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"Dionysus Last Supper\", \"from\": 31663, \"to\": 31688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And in a country where a perceived insult to Mohammed was handled by murdering the publisher, would not civil discussion of the issue be a less hateful response?\", \"from\": 31708, \"to\": 31869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 31715, \"to\": 31724}, {\"ngram\": \"a perceived insult\", \"from\": 31731, \"to\": 31749}, {\"ngram\": \"Mohammed\", \"from\": 31753, \"to\": 31761}, {\"ngram\": \"the publisher\", \"from\": 31787, \"to\": 31800}, {\"ngram\": \"not civil discussion\", \"from\": 31808, \"to\": 31828}, {\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 31832, \"to\": 31841}, {\"ngram\": \"a less hateful response\", \"from\": 31845, \"to\": 31868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seems there has been many quotes from participants in this shambolic event confirming that it was a parody of the last supper and now they only want tolerance.\", \"from\": 31871, \"to\": 32030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many quotes\", \"from\": 31892, \"to\": 31903}, {\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 31909, \"to\": 31921}, {\"ngram\": \"this shambolic event\", \"from\": 31925, \"to\": 31945}, {\"ngram\": \"a parody\", \"from\": 31969, \"to\": 31977}, {\"ngram\": \"the last supper\", \"from\": 31981, \"to\": 31996}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 32020, \"to\": 32029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their hypocrisy is without bounds and they should receive as much tolerance as they showed.\", \"from\": 32031, \"to\": 32122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their hypocrisy\", \"from\": 32031, \"to\": 32046}, {\"ngram\": \"bounds\", \"from\": 32058, \"to\": 32064}, {\"ngram\": \"as much tolerance\", \"from\": 32089, \"to\": 32106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If anything, in present day France, they should have criminal charges lodged against them for the mocking and degrading of a religion.\", \"from\": 32123, \"to\": 32257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32151, \"end\": 32157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.8237582588439206, \"rank\": 0.1920406411157502, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 32126, \"to\": 32134}, {\"ngram\": \"present day\", \"from\": 32139, \"to\": 32150}, {\"ngram\": \"criminal charges\", \"from\": 32176, \"to\": 32192}, {\"ngram\": \"the mocking\", \"from\": 32217, \"to\": 32228}, {\"ngram\": \"degrading\", \"from\": 32233, \"to\": 32242}, {\"ngram\": \"a religion\", \"from\": 32246, \"to\": 32256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Mr. LePen can be charged for calling the Romani smelly, or a teenager charged for calling Islam a \\\"religion of hate\\\" or Ms Bardot can be charged, then surely, under French law, these so-called performers should be charged for mocking and thereby slandering and degrading a religion.Now if this event were in the United States I would say nothing except turn off the TV, and not watch another minute of Olympic coverage (which I am doing anyway) but I am looking at precedent under French Law and even under the Napoleonic Code it should remain consistent, should it not.As an alternative I would suggest repeating the event and let every French Citizen or Olympic Games ticket holder come to the repeat event and being allowed to throw pies, of any flavor, at the participants in the event, from a distance of about 5 feet.\", \"from\": 32258, \"to\": 33085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 32265, \"end\": 32270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823037, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LePen\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LEPEN_(political_party)\"}, {\"begin\": 32302, \"end\": 32308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romani_people\", \"score\": 0.9999561204433933, \"rank\": 2.7697679785121347e-05, \"text\": \"Romani\", \"types\